													<tr><td valign="top" width="100%">&nbsp;<br>
													<!-- strMainData goes here-->
													<table align='center' cellpadding=5 width='85%'>  <tr><td class='header' bgcolor='black' width='100%'>PALADIN STRATEGIES AND PLAYGUIDES</td></tr>  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'><font class='spti'>A FEW MISSED THINGS ABOUT PVP.</font> - <small>Dirhum, Vallon Zek</td></tr>
  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'><p>Hail,<br>
<br>
<br>

---------------<br>
<br>
Flash of Light:<br>
<br>
This spell seems like an instant win for a paladin, but remember this. Even if you hit a blinded melee opponent, even from behind (assuming he has auto attack on) HE CAN STILL HIT YOU.<br>
<br>
What you need to do is PvP Joust, hes how.<br>
<br>
Blind him, make sure auto-attack is off. Pick a target past him, and run for it, so you run straight past him, when you think you are in good range... hit auto attack, then quickly hit it again to turn it off. This will hit him, and he wont have the chance to hit back... Don't forget to reblind and root if you are sufficent level. It was stated that rooting a melee is foolish. It is IMPERATIVE. You don't want your opponent running around like a chicken, you want a nice solid target to joust down.<br>
<br>
Monks/Rogues:<br>
<br>
These guys are tricky, remember they can both disarm and instill doubt.<br>
<br>
For disarm, set up hot keys for your primary/secondary slots, and your generals... that way you can whip your weapon back in your hand, making his/her attempt to embarass you useless.<br>
<br>
(For Hot Keying: Click "i" to active inventory. Then click and hold the box "primary" and carry it ove to the open spaces (hot key boxes) on the left side of your screen and click once again to place it. Repeat for your general slots (make sure you dont have alot of room or else it the weapon may go in a bag) )<br>
<br>
Another deadly weapon is instill doubt, for this your going to gave to blind/root/joust them down. If you have a shield bash them once and a while, to keep them from thinking.<br>
<br>
Shadowknights:<br>
<br>
Playing a shadowknight also I feel this is a class to be warned about, they can snare, dot, shadowstep out when blinded, even rooted. not to mention harmtouch.. so dont get cocky with the LoH.<br>
<br>
Of course MR is a given, but heres some strategys that should keep you on the winning side.<br>
<br>
ROOT: avoid him from meleeing you, now you just have to deal with second rate necro spells.<br>
<br>
BLIND: somepeople still dont use hotkeys for casting, this eliminates them.<br>
<br>
HOLY MIGHT: if your low on health, dont want to joust (incase the sk is hitting his HT button hoping to get you when in range) then finish him off with your low lvl nuke, holy might.<br>
<br>
If you dont have it, your going to have to either take your chances and joust, or reblind/root and heal yourself.<br>
<br>
General: If you are facing a melee, always root him and heal yourself, this takes any damage he/she has delt.. and laughs in its face.<br>
<br>
Don't smack talk: I recommend disabling ooc/shout channels because the complaining you'll get from the person you killed will just aggrovate you.<br>
<br>
Remember, paladin is by no means a pvp class. We have nice utilitys.. but dont think blind/root will win everytime. So, if a necro gets beats from you... Leave it at that, if hes smart he will hang his head in shame wishing he fought on the other side of the war.<br>
<br>
<br>I cannot help with tactics over 22, though I do have a cleric and I must say holy might is nice and effective.
<br></p>


		</td></tr>
